# Security Rules

- **Always sanitize inputs** (API, forms, file uploads)
- Prevent **SQL injection**: use parameterized queries or ORM; never concatenate user input into SQL
- Prevent **path traversal**: validate and sanitize file paths; do not use user input as paths
- Prevent **XSS**: escape output; use safe templating and CSP where applicable
- **Never log** passwords, tokens, or other sensitive data
- **Never store** passwords in plain text; use strong hashing (e.g. bcrypt, argon2)
- Use secure authentication (e.g. JWT with short expiry, secure cookies)
- **Validate file uploads**: type, size, and content; store outside web root when possible
- Use **rate limiting** on public and auth-related APIs

Avoid dangerous operations (eval, exec with user input, unsafe deserialization).
